item.title: Impossible Problem
item.dc:creator: @revanet revanet
item.description:
@revanet wrote:

[quote=“Jingojohn, post:12, topic:353887”]What version your JDK is, change it to that in the compiler. My version is jdk1.6.0_17.

Go to C:\Program Files\Java\

It will say what the version of JDK you have. Go to your compiler, right-click, edit, replace the numbers on your JDK to the version you have.

This is my compiler. I replaced some of my variables. They were just the names of the client.

@echo off :menu title "Client Name" Compiler - Made by JingoJohn @echo Compiling Client... if exist "%programfiles%\Java" (call :compile "%programfiles%\Java\") else (goto error) :compile for /D %%x in ("%~1jdk*") do (set p="%%~x\bin\javac.exe") if defined p (%p% -cp . *.java) if defined p (goto end) :error echo You do not have Java installed. Please download it at the site that is about to load. "%programfiles%\InternetExplorer\iexplore.exe" http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp :end echo Client Compiled! pause exit [/quote]
They way the source he has is set up that won’t work.
